hints_latex:
The cross product formula can be interpreted using determinants:

\begin{align*}
\mathbf{u\times v}=\begin{vmatrix}
\mathbf{i}&\mathbf{j}&\mathbf{k}\\
u_1&u_2&u_3\\
v_1&v_2&v_3\\
\end{vmatrix}
\end{align*}

sols_latex:
By the cross product formula,

\begin{align*}
a \times b &=\begin{vmatrix}
\mathbf{i}&\mathbf{j}&\mathbf{k}\\
-3&-3&3\\
2&-3&-2\\
\end{vmatrix} \\
&= \begin{vmatrix}
-3&3\\
-3&-2
\end{vmatrix}\mathbf{i}
-\begin{vmatrix}
-3&3\\
2&-2
\end{vmatrix}\mathbf{j}
+\begin{vmatrix}
-3&-3\\
2&-3
\end{vmatrix}\mathbf{k} \\
&= 15 \mathbf{i} - 0 \mathbf{j} + 15\mathbf{k} \\
&= \begin{bmatrix}
15 \\ 0 \\ 15
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

